Project Folder Structure
This structure separates concerns into backend (server, models, routes) and frontend (static files, though we'll combine the main interface into a single HTML file for this project).
budget-tracker-app/
├── node_modules/         # Node.js dependencies
├── .env                  # Environment variables (DB credentials, secrets)
├── package.json          # Project dependencies and scripts
├── server.js             # Main application entry point (Express setup)
├── db/
│   └── db.js             # MySQL connection pool setup
├── models/
│   ├── UserModel.js      # Handles Person/User data and DB interactions
│   ├── FundsModel.js     # Handles Wallet/Fund data and transactions
│   └── InvestmentModel.js# Handles Investment data
├── routes/
│   ├── AuthRoutes.js     # /api/auth routes (register, login)
│   ├── FundsRoutes.js    # /api/funds routes (record spend/earn, budget plan)
│   └── InvestmentRoutes.js# /api/investment routes (choose investment, get insights)
├── sql/
│   └── schema.sql        # Database schema definition
└── public/
    └── index.html        # Single-file frontend template (Dashboard & Investments)
